iduous mountain forest, invariably above 600 m (2,000 ft), although it is not common below 900 m (3,000 ft). The main breeding season is in March and April, but a second brood is often reared later in the year. The cup-shaped nest is a lined compact mass of moss. The site is usually a well-shaded rock ledge. The normal clutch is two or three brown-spotted pink eggs are laid. This is relatively easy bird to see, despite its forest habitat. It feeds mainly on flying insects, beetles, caterpillars and other insects, but also eats berries. In Culture This bird appears in 50 Sri Lankan rupee bank note (2010 series). References Birds of India by Grimmett, Inskipp and Inskipp, ISBN 0-691-04910-6", "shortSummary": "The dull-blue flycatcher (Eumyias sordidus) is a small passerine bird in the flycatcher family, Muscicapidae. This species is an endemic re…", "locations": ["森林"], "habitats": ["山地森林"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/97/Dull-blue_flycatcher.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-eumyias", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-eumyias", "species": "taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus"}, "expandable": true, "x": -95.05, "y": -396.54, "z": -213.32}], "links": [{"key": "bird-dull-blue-flycatcher-b27d1586__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus", "source": "bird-dull-blue-flycatcher-b27d1586", "target": "taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-eumyias", "source": "taxonomy-species-eumyias-sordidus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-eumyias", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 b